units and measurents 





plane angle: unit radian
the angle between the two radi of a circle which cut of from the circumfrance an arh equal to the length of the radius


solid angle : unit steradian 
                it is the solid angle with its apex at the center of a sphere that cuts out an area on the  surface of the sphere equal to the area of the square whose sides are equal to the radius of the sphere. solid angle is equal to area cut out from the surface of the sphere divided by radius square.
                
